        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:11PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 311 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Elbert, or 39 miles southeast of Denver, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elbert and Fondis.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
